Looking deep into the eyes of the audience  you dont have to speak Portuguese to be completely entranced, its universal! Linikers music speaks for itself but her presence on the stage is part of a greater movement. Check the AltLatino NPR article.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul style=\"line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify;\" ><span >The band rose to prominence in October 2015 with the YouTube release CRU, followed by their award-winning and lauded September 2016 studio album, Remonta. After wowing crowds in Austin at SXSW in both 2017 and 2018, this summer marks Linikers first performance in Canada!<\/span><\/hatul><hatul style=\"line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify;\" ><span >Co-presented by Uma Nota Culture, Lula Music ad Arts and Polyphonic Ground in association with Sarau Brazil.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul style=\"line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify;\" ><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a dataquery=\"#txtMedia1quh\"><span style=\"\">Visit the event page<\/span><\/a><\/span><span >.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul style=\"line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify;\" ><span >Doors Open: 7:00pm \/ Show Starts: 8:30pm.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul style=\"line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify;\" ><span >Very limited early-bird tickets $20 **** SOLD OUT ****<\/span><\/hatul><hatul style=\"line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify;\" ><span >Regular Advance Tickets $33.50. <\/span><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a dataquery=\"#txtMediacuv\"><span style=\"\">Available online here<\/span><\/a><\/span><span >.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul style=\"line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify;\" ><span >Dinner reservations guarantee seating.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul><span style=\"\"><span >Reserve for dinner <\/span><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a dataquery=\"#txtMedia19da\"><span style=\"\">online<\/span><\/a><\/span><span style=\"\"> <\/span><span >or call - 416.588.0307. The design of this mural brought together diverse members of the west end area to create a visual celebration of the contributions of both our local artistic community and artists with roots in South America to the cultural life of the Dundas West neighbourhood. Painting of this mural began, in the context of the recent Dundas West Street Festival (2018 Edition).<\/span><\/hatul><hatul><span >A beautiful art work, but also much more than that, this project engaged youth from communities within the Dundas West Area in educational and mural painting workshops at Alexander Muir Public School, in which artists from Valparaiso, Chile, had the opportunity to work with students and community members to explore the issues and designs as part of the mural creation process.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul><span >Located at 1533 Dundas St. West, this dramatic and impressive mural was produced by Rodrigo Ardiles, and painted by Toronto artists Jieun Kim and Erika James along with international artists Giovanni Zamora and Pablo Gomez. This collaborative effort,<\/span><\/hatul><hatul><span >another showpiece for the Dundas West Area, celebrates music and arts, and reinforces Torontos reputation as a centre of creativity and innovation  Diversity Our Strength.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul><span >This initiative builds on mural art already created in our neighbourhood with the Dundas West BIA. These public art works, have been included in many guided walking tours, help promote sustainable and creative economic growth and support the creation of a local Public Street Art Museum in Toronto. This project is supported and funded by the City of Toronto - StreetARToronto Program, Toronto Arts Council, Canadian Embassy in Chile, Chilean Consulate in Toronto, Municipality of Valparaiso, Chile, Dundas West BIA &amp; Museum, Lula Music and Arts Centre, Creativo Arts Collective, CASAT, TDSB, Memorial Museum of Chile and the Valparaiso En Colores Initiative.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul><span >We extend the invitation to the entire community to participate in our public inauguration and celebration of the vibrant creative neighbourhood of Dundas West<\/span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><span >.<\/span><\/span><\/hatul><hatul><span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><span >Event info: <\/span><\/span><span >Sunday, June 10 at 1533 Dundas St. West. 10:00 am. <\/span><\/hatul><hatul><span >For more information call 416 588 0307.<\/span><\/hatul>","links":[],"version":3},"author":"","coverImageData":{"_type":"CoverImageData","coverImageType":"photo","video":{"_type":"wix:Video","videoId":"","videoType":"","thumbnail":""},"photo":{"_type":"wix:Image","title":"","src":"cd6115_a942b1904b9b406890834d26d739944c~mv2.jpg","width":1000,"height":1333},"isHD":false,"isHeroImage":false},"description":{"_type":"wix:RichText","text":"","links":[],"version":1},"mobileTitle":"&quot;Toronto &amp; 2 at Dundas West Fest.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul >Each year the LULAWORLD festival showcases new work and collaborations by local and international Latin, Brazilian, jazz, folk and global artists. In addition to three CD releases, highlights of this years festival include a residency with Olodum member Mestre Memeo Memeu direct from Brazil, Indigenous reggae rock and blues by Shauit and Digging Roots, Philadelphia-based spoken word\/jazz poet Ursula Rucker, and a music and mural exchange with Valparaiso, Chile. We invite everyone to join in: take a dance lesson, perform in our Street Brass band, and enjoy take in music with roots from around the globe.<\/hatul><hatul >For all shows, dinner reservations guarantee seating. Dinner and show packages available Fridays and Saturdays. tropical heritage of MPB, resulting in a beautiful, emotional and energetic show. Linikers music speaks for itself but her presence on the stage is part of a greater movement. Check the AltLatino NPR article.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul style=\"line-height: 1.5em; text-align: justify;\" ><span >The band rose to prominence in October 2015 with the YouTube release CRU, followed by their award-winning and lauded September 2016 studio album, Remonta. Valparaiso: Creative Cities Cultural Exchange&quot; - Mural Inauguration","categoryIds":[],"date":{"_type":"wix:Date","iso":"2018-06-09T03:16:16.850Z"},"text":{"_type":"wix:RichText","text":"<hatul><span >You are invited to join in celebrating an exciting new, large scale community mural supported by the Lula Music &amp; Arts Centre and installed by Chile based Creativo Arts Collective in collaboration with Toronto based street artists, on Dundas West. The design of this mural brought together diverse members of the west end area to create a visual celebration of the contributions of both our local artistic community and artists with roots in South America to the cultural life of the Dundas West neighbourhood. Painting of this mural began, in the context of the recent Dundas West Street Festival (2018 Edition).<\/span><\/hatul><hatul><span >A beautiful art work, but also much more than that, this project engaged youth from communities within the Dundas West Area in educational and mural painting workshops at Alexander Muir Public School, in which artists from Valparaiso, Chile, had the opportunity to work with students and community members to explore the issues and designs as part of the mural creation process.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul><span >Located at 1533 Dundas St. West, this dramatic and impressive mural was produced by Rodrigo Ardiles, and painted by Toronto artists Jieun Kim and Erika James along with international artists Giovanni Zamora and Pablo Gomez. This collaborative effort,<\/span><\/hatul><hatul><span >another showpiece for the Dundas West Area, celebrates music and arts, and reinforces Torontos reputation as a centre of creativity and innovation  Diversity Our Strength.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul><span >This initiative builds on mural art already created in our neighbourhood with the Dundas West BIA. These public art works, have been included in many guided walking tours, help promote sustainable and creative economic growth and support the creation of a local Public Street Art Museum in Toronto. This project is supported and funded by the City of Toronto - StreetARToronto Program, Toronto Arts Council, Canadian Embassy in Chile, Chilean Consulate in Toronto, Municipality of Valparaiso, Chile, Dundas West BIA &amp; Museum, Lula Music and Arts Centre, Creativo Arts Collective, CASAT, TDSB, Memorial Museum of Chile and the Valparaiso En Colores Initiative.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul><span >We extend the invitation to the entire community to participate in our public inauguration and celebration of the vibrant creative neighbourhood of Dundas West<\/span><span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><span >.<\/span><\/span><\/hatul><hatul><span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><span >Event info: <\/span><\/span><span >Sunday, June 10 at 1533 Dundas St. West. 10:00 am. <\/span><\/hatul><hatul><span >For more information call 416 588 0307.<\/span><\/hatul>","links":[],"version":3},"author":"","coverImageData":{"_type":"CoverImageData","coverImageType":"photo","video":{"_type":"wix:Video","videoId":"","videoType":"","thumbnail":""},"photo":{"_type":"wix:Image","title":"","src":"cd6115_a942b1904b9b406890834d26d739944c~mv2.jpg","width":1000,"height":1333},"isHD":false,"isHeroImage":false},"description":{"_type":"wix:RichText","text":"","links":[],"version":1},"mobileTitle":"&quot;Toronto &amp; 2 at Dundas West Fest.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul >Each year the LULAWORLD festival showcases new work and collaborations by local and international Latin, Brazilian, jazz, folk and global artists. In addition to three CD releases, highlights of this years festival include a residency with Olodum member Mestre Memeo Memeu direct from Brazil, Indigenous reggae rock and blues by Shauit and Digging Roots, Philadelphia-based spoken word\/jazz poet Ursula Rucker, and a music and mural exchange with Valparaiso, Chile. We invite everyone to join in: take a dance lesson, perform in our Street Brass band, and enjoy take in music with roots from around the globe.<\/hatul><hatul >For all shows, dinner reservations guarantee seating. Dinner and show packages available Fridays and Saturdays. Email <span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a dataquery=\"#txtMedia95t\">info@lula.ca<\/a><\/span> or call 416 588 0307.<\/hatul><hatul ><br>\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Thursday May 31<br>\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a dataquery=\"#txtMedia1c66\"><span style=\"\">LULAWORLD 2018 Opening Night<\/span><\/a><\/span><br>\nCo-presented with CIUT and Exclaim!<\/span><\/hatul><hatul ><span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Doors 7pm concert 8pm *&nbsp;<a dataquery=\"#txtMedia1zlj\"><span style=\"\">$15 advance<\/span><\/a>&nbsp;\/ $20 at door \/ a la carte menu \/ dinner reservations guarantee seating.&nbsp;@Lula Lounge.&nbsp;<\/span>&nbsp;LULAWORLD 2018 kicks off with special guests direct from Chile, Colombia and Brazil.<\/hatul><hatul ><span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Paloma Castro<\/span><\/hatul><hatul >As part of an ongoing cultural exchange with our sister organization in Chile, Valparaiso en Colores, multi-instrumentalist Paloma Castro performs with Ernesto Espinoza, Ruben Esguerra and Luis Orbegoso.<\/hatul><hatul ><br>\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Leang Manjarrs + Ruben Esguerra &amp; New Tradition<\/span><br>\nA master gaitero at the forefront of Colombias Nueva Gaita movement explores diverse Caribbean folkloric traditions alongside Esguerras JUNO-nominated Toronto ensemble, creating an empowering, hip hop-infused expression of indigenous and Afro-Colombian music.<\/hatul><hatul ><span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Mestre Memeu with T. Dot Batu<\/span><\/hatul><hatul >This tightly knit Toronto Afro-Brazilian samba reggae percussion group is joined by a leading member and educator from the legendary Afro-Brazilian bloco Olodum as part of a week-long residency.<\/hatul><hatul ><br>\n<span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">LULAWORLD @ DUNDAS WEST FEST<\/span><\/span><\/hatul><hatul ><span style=\"\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">FRIDAY JUNE 1 &amp; SATURDAY JUNE 2<\/span><\/span><br>\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">LULAWORLD&nbsp;takes to the streets for a day and two music and dance filled nights.<\/span>&nbsp;<br>\nDundas West Fest is a local celebration of creativity and diversity that strives to be participatory and inclusive. Known as the festival that kicks off Torontos summer festival season, its the perfect opportunity to invite out-of-town guests to experience and be part Torontos exciting multiculturalism.<\/hatul><hatul >The community street party gives us a chance to share highlights of the indoor Lulaworld&nbsp;festival in a free outdoor setting. In addition to enjoying the 80+&nbsp;&nbsp;musicians who will appear on the Lulaworld stage <span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a dataquery=\"#txtMedia1teu\"><span style=\"\">(at 1630 Dundas West) <\/span><\/a><\/span>over the two days, visitors can participate in a brass band, take&nbsp;music and dance workshops, help paint a community mural and enjoy food and drinks from around the world.&nbsp;<\/hatul><hatul ><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a dataquery=\"#txtMedia13jq\"><span style=\"\">See full details here<\/span><span >!<\/span><\/a><\/span><\/hatul><hatul ><br>\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">June 1<br>\n<span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a dataquery=\"#txtMediabi1\"><span style=\"\">Rojitas and Yani Borrell<\/span><\/a><\/span><br>\nCo-presented with Latinos Magazine<\/span><\/hatul><hatul ><span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Doors 6:30pm, dance lesson 9pm, concert 10:30 * $15 at the door \/ $57 dinner, dance lesson &amp; show package.&nbsp;@Lula Lounge.<\/span><br>\nKnown respectively as Cubas Golden Voice and El Elegante, two of Torontos most celebrated Cuban singers come together to present a night of shared repertoire backed by a full salsa orchestra.<\/hatul><hatul ><br>\nSaturday June 2<br>\n<span style=\"font-weight:bold;\"><span style=\"text-decoration:underline;\"><a dataquery=\"#txtMedia12f8\"><span style=\"\">Yan Collazo (Puerto Rico) with Sean Bellaviti &amp; Conjunto Lacalu<\/span><\/a><\/span><br>\nCo-presented with Toronto Hispano<\/span><\/hatul><hatul ><span style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Doors 6:30pm, dance lesson 9pm, concert 10:30 *&nbsp;<a dataquery=\"#txtMedia20zs\"><span style=\"\">$30 advance<\/span><\/a>&nbsp;\/ $40 at the door \/ $69 dinner &amp; show package&nbsp;@Lula Lounge.<\/span><\/hatul><hatul ><br>\nDirect from San Juan, Puerto Rico, Latin Grammy-nominee Yan Collazo joins leading players from the Toronto salsa scene for a one-night-only special performance.
